[ANALYSIS]
The experiment "bow_opt_20260514_170905_run_04" using a Bag of Words (BoW) architecture achieved a success status with an F1 score of 0.7188 and accuracy of 0.775, indicating that the model performed reasonably well on the validation set. However, the experiment encountered several issues related to chained assignment errors in the pandas library, specifically when attempting to fill missing values in the 'keyword', 'location', and 'text' columns using the `fillna` method with `inplace=True`. These errors suggest that the operations were not being applied directly to the original DataFrame due to how pandas handles Copy-on-Write. For the next run, it is recommended to address these issues by modifying the code to avoid chained assignment or by ensuring that the operations are performed on the original DataFrame without using `inplace=True`, thus preventing potential data integrity problems and improving the reliability of the experiment.